9
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:32,119
♫ Never knew… what this word truly felt like ♫

10
00:00:32,119 --> 00:00:36,680
♫ In all the life I've lived, there’s never been a single time ♫

11
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:40,080
♫ That anyone has ever entered my heart ♫

12
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:47,480
♫ But today, meeting you has started to make me wonder ♫

13
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:52,560
♫ What is this feeling? My heart begins to tremble ♫

14
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:55,560
♫ And I just can't control it ♫

15
00:00:56,480 --> 00:01:00,160
♫ What happened to my heart right now? ♫

16
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:04,120
♫ I can’t control it when you’re around ♫

17
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:10,039
♫ This heart of mine, it has stopped at you ♫

18
00:01:11,039 --> 00:01:15,640
♫ Or is this love? That’s what they call it, right? ♫

19
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:18,520
♫ When my heart begins to soften ♫

20
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:23,200
♫ Like a stream, soothing my heart at every moment ♫

21
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:26,360
♫ From morning until I go to bed, all I see is you ♫

22
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:31,039
♫ Or is this love? Are you the one? ♫

23
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:34,479
♫ The one heaven meant for me to find ♫

24
00:01:34,479 --> 00:01:38,320
♫ Is that really the truth? Is it you? ♫

25
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:41,520
♫ I want to know, because you’ve come into my heart ♫

26
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:46,520
(The Water)
♫ I want to know, because you’ve come into my heart ♫

27
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:28,400
Be quiet, if you don’t wanna get hurt.

28
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,920
Nuch! Nuch!

29
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:21,520
Oh my!

30
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,520
Quick, Nuch!

31
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:32,720
Does it come off? Oh! There too. Wipe it off, quickly.

32
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:38,720
I’m sorry, sir. We’ll finish cleaning as soon as possible.

33
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:44,240
Does it come off? Wipe it again. The guests might complain if they see it.

34
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,760
Oh! I’m sorry, sir. Sorry.

35
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,840
Will it leave a mark?

36
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,200
Is it dry?

37
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:55,000
I wonder what kind of stain it is.

38
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,880
Go!

39
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:11,920
Let me go!

40
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:12,600
Sit!

41
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,680
Let me go! Why are you arresting me?

42
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,560
Excuse me, Boss.

43
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:34,560
Hello. I am Apo Watinwanich,

44
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:40,840
an Executive Vice President of the Monarch Global International Hotel under the Watin Group.

45
00:04:42,159 --> 00:04:46,360
First of all, please accept my apologies for a sudden surprise and disruption.

46
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,880
The incident earlier wasn’t real.

47
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:54,920
It was a joint training with the officers to test our security system…

48
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,880
in response to an emergency event which may possibly occur at the hotel.

49
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:02,280
It is our top priority to ensure the safety of our guests.

50
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:06,080
This kind of training is very common among international hotels.

51
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:10,200
So that our guests can be assured, that in case of emergency,

52
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:14,600
our employees as well as the security guards…

53
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:17,760
will take the best care of you and protect you from all harms.

54
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:22,800
I sincerely appreciate your kind understanding and cooperation.

55
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:27,920
We promise to try our best to deliver an excellent service during your stay at the hotel,

56
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:31,200
and make it safe, cozy, and the most pleasant experience for everyone.

57
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,880
Miss Preem.

58
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,360
It wasn’t good enough.

59
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:04,240
Right after you were taken hold of, those guards in the CCTV control room called the police immediately.

60
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,800
While waiting for the police,

61
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:10,160
Miss Wadee and other employees also acted normal to buy time,

62
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:12,960
and keep the suspect unaware that the police were coming.

63
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:15,280
What did we do wrong then, Boss?

64
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:21,360
This wouldn’t have happened at all if there were a security guard in that area.

65
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,480
Where was he?

66
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,600
Miss Wadee!

67
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:38,480
Miss Wadee! Now, I know where that security guard disappeared to!

68
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,280
To make up with his girlfriend, right?

69
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,880
You really know it all!

70
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:48,360
So, will he get sacked?

71
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:53,440
Hmm, no idea. Miss Preem said Boss is considering it.

72
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,800
Boss might be very strict but she isn’t mean.

73
00:06:56,800 --> 00:07:00,160
She’ll probably give him a second chance and won’t fire him.

74
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,560
Who knows?

75
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:06,920
She might often give people a second chance. But there’ll never be a third time.

76
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:10,040
Besides, it has something to do with the hotel’s reputation this time.

77
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:13,360
I don’t think she’d let him off the hook so easily.

78
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,680
Jah!

79
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,880
I’m sorry, Miss. Sorry.

80
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,320
I’m sorry.

81
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,560
Be careful next time. / - Yes.

82
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:55,840
That was close.

83
00:07:57,320 --> 00:08:01,560
But you know what? Despite being so dedicated in work,

84
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:04,560
Some people still believe she got her position because she’s an only child.

85
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:08,320
And since she’s a woman, they even doubt if she can work at all.

86
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:14,880
Can or cannot, our hotel has won an award every year.

87
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:17,880
Can those who do nothing but look down at others do that too?

88
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:23,480
Honestly, if our boss is a little less stern…

89
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:27,200
and doesn’t work 24/7, that would’ve been great. It’s too tiring!

90
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:34,320
She only lives to work. Who else could’ve made her think otherwise?

91
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:39,120
For today, you’re scheduled to meet with the marketing team at 1pm.

92
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,919
And at 3pm, you have another meeting with the HR team.

93
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:44,600
In the evening, you have a dinner appointment with Mr. Wichian.

94
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,720
Is there anything else you need…

95
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,000
Hey! Watch where you’re going!

96
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:01,960
I’m sorry. Are you all right?

97
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:08,400
I’m fine. But I don’t think my phone is.

98
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:14,400
I’m terribly sorry indeed.

99
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:18,200
About the compensation, I’ll have my secretary take care of it.

100
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:24,400
Miss Preem, I’ll leave it to you. I have to go for a meeting.

101
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,160
Hey, wait! Hold on! Hey!

102
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:28,080
Get back here and talk first! Hey! / - Miss!

103
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,320
Miss! Miss!

104
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:34,320
My apologies for the damage, Miss. If you want to repair it or buy a new one,

105
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:37,120
please feel free to let me know.

106
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,720
Here is my LINE QR code.

107
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:47,320
So, is that how Apo Watinwanich, the owner of a five-star hotel,

108
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,400
treat her guests?

109
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:52,360
You know her, Miss?

110
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,440
I’ve stayed here for 3 whole days waiting to see her.

111
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,920
But it all ended in less than 3 minutes!

112
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:07,560
Nade, am I not pretty?

113
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:08,880
How’s that related?

114
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:12,640
Can’t you see? I’m all dressed up like this…

115
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:15,240
but she just walked into me and didn’t even glance at me.

116
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:19,280
Are my brows uneven, eye shadows too dark, lips colour too plain, or…

117
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,840
Are my boobs not big enough?

118
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:25,360
Maybe she isn’t into girls.

119
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:29,960
Listen. I’ve done some digging around.

120
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:33,960
I’m pretty sure she’s into women.

121
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:39,560
Geez, the screen is broken. Give me the ipad.

122
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:45,800
Look!

123
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:54,480
This is Kasama, Apo’s cousin. She just got married. This is her wife.

124
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,760
This one is Wayo.

125
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:02,840
Definitely a girl kisser. She used to date Pui, the belle at my accounting faculty.

126
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:06,240
I know because I once had to work on a project with her.

127
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:12,360
And this one is Utchima. No records of dating men or any interest in men.

128
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:18,040
Judging from this info, I’d say the whole Watinwanich family is definitely into girls.

129
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:20,120
I’m one hundred percent…no, one million percent sure!

130
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:24,840
Neh, my sister loves grilled pork but I don’t eat it ever.

131
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:29,000
You can’t assume they’re all into girls just because they’re cousins.

132
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,120
I don’t think your plan would work.

133
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,520
Well then…

134
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,360
let’s use another plan.

135
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,120
What plan?

136
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:44,920
You even went out of your way and got yourself checked in at this hotel just to discredit her. Did it work though?

137
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:49,920
Or are you going to complain about how the room here is luxurious but lovely.

138
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:53,200
And the price is also reasonable, not a rip-off like we expected.

139
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:58,520
Nade! I asked you to help me complain about her hotel, not about me!

140
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:02,200
What? If you did the right thing, I sure wouldn’t be complaining.

141
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:05,360
But right now, what you’re doing is nonsense!

142
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,240
Nonsense, what? Who said nonsense?

143
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,600
It’s not nonsense at all!

144
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:14,080
Just admit it…that the Watin Group’s hotel is top-notch. You can’t do anything to them.

145
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,240
You sound exactly like my dad.

146
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,840
[A week earlier]

147
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,440
I’m sorry, Dad.

148
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:36,080
Sorry? You know…

149
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:40,000
if your apologies could be converted into money,

150
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,800
I would’ve been the richest man in the country.

151
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:50,800
You made it sound so fancy, promising me a big success.

152
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,240
But look what it turns out to be? A complete mess!

153
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:58,520
But I didn’t mess up the land bidding, Dad.

154
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:02,640
You didn’t? Then how come the land that’s supposed to be mine…

155
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:05,320
has now fallen into the hands of the Watin Group?

156
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:11,560
He said they’re playing favourites, Dad.

157
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,800
It’s none of your business.

158
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:17,280
Pat, you should learn from your brother.

159
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:20,600
No matter what job I assign to him, he’s never let me down.

160
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:27,040
And look what you did. Of all the people in this world, you have to lose to that Adisorn’s daughter.

161
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:31,400
You know what? Why don’t you just put on a skirt instead?

162
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,400
Dad, isn’t that too harsh?

163
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:41,760
A girl like you who doesn’t know how to work should better keep your mouth shut.

164
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,440
You’ve never given me a chance to work with the Wachara Group.

165
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,920
How do you know I can’t work?

166
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:55,320
If I let you do that, my company would have gone bankrupt.

167
00:13:55,680 --> 00:14:02,040
Your only job is to get married to the man I see fit. The one I’ve approved of.

168
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:04,840
Just use your pretty face…

169
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:09,320
to support our company and make it grow bigger and bigger.

170
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:14,440
For jobs that require brains and knowledge, just let the boys handle them.

171
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,560
How was it, dear?

172
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:37,160
When will Dad stop judging me?

173
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:41,160
I told you it’s not your fault. It’s mine.

174
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:43,360
Because you’re his mistress?

175
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:47,120
It’s not your fault, Mum. You didn’t have a choice.

176
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:50,960
Lada, please forgive him, dear.

177
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:55,280
He has taken good care of us all this time, never left us to struggle on our own.

178
00:14:56,160 --> 00:15:00,880
Take care? By making us live in the shadows like this?

179
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,560
He’s never told anyone you’re his wife.

180
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:05,880
Never called me a daughter.

181
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:08,120
And even forbid me to use his surname.

182
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:12,520
I have to use your surname, Kunarnon, instead. You call that ‘take care’?

183
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:20,840
Lada, I’m begging you. Despite all that, he’s the person we should be grateful for.

184
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:27,840
So, do I have to let him marry me off in order to show gratitude to him?

185
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:33,400
[Pheempat]: You want to work with Wachara Group, Lada?

186
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:46,240
Lada, I know you want to help your brother.

187
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:50,000
But this is something big. It won’t be that easy.

188
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:54,360
I’ll do it anyway.

189
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:59,080
The Watin Group played dirty during the bidding and snatched the land from him.

190
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,920
I’ll get back at them.

191
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:07,440
But trying to get close to Miss Apo to steal information from her for your brother?

192
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:09,760
How does that make you different from them?

193
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:14,880
Well, if I succeed, Dad will finally see…

194
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:18,120
that a daughter like me isn’t just an object for marriage.

195
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:22,000
That I can also be much more and do many things for the family, like what his sons do.

196
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,240
What’s next?

197
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:35,080
A meeting about a party arrangement.

198
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,000
What party?

199
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:41,320
A party to celebrate your winning of the Next Icon Hotel Ashley award for 3 years in a row.

200
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:44,800
It’s an award voted by those from the hotel business industry. We have to...

201
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,480
Cancel it.

202
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:48,000
Yes?

203
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,800
How many years have you been working as my secretary?

204
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:57,120
How is it that you don’t know which job I would or wouldn’t do to waste my time in life?

205
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:03,720
I’m sorry, Boss. It’s just that you recently won the bidding on the land,

206
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:07,880
and also won this award. So I thought you might want to relax a bit and came up with this party.

207
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:11,440
Those successes happened because of everyone.

208
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:14,920
Keep the budget for the year-end bonus instead.

209
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,720
What’s next on schedule?

210
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,599
The big boss’ secretary said her boss wants you to…

211
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:21,760
Tell my dad to go on those blind dates himself.

212
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:25,680
Are you sure you want me to tell him that, Boss?

213
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:41,480
Yeah, I told my secretary to tell him exactly that.

214
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:44,280
Maybe he’d finally give up.

215
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:48,840
Wait, don’t tell me he called Mum?

216
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:53,160
[Fah]: Uncle is just worried. He’s afraid you’d be too consumed with work and forget to live your life.

217
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,840
Mum’s also worried about you.

218
00:17:56,480 --> 00:18:00,320
Please tell Mum not to take what Dad says seriously.

219
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:02,800
I’m quite happy with work.

220
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:08,400
Anyway, how are you? Since when did you move back to live with Mum?

221
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:11,160
Well, I had spent 8 months working in Mongolia.

222
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:16,360
Once done, I decided to come back for a break. But turns out it’s not a break at all.

223
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:21,440
[Fah]: Mum and Dad keep complaining every day that I should change my job. They say it’s too dangerous.

224
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:26,000
But I like meeting new people. It’s challenging.

225
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:29,440
I know how you feel.

226
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:36,040
When we were kids, Dad and Mum often told us to pay attention in class…

227
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:38,360
[Apo]: so that we could grow up and do the job we love.

228
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:43,760
But now that we get to do what we love, they can’t help but still complain.

229
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:52,840
But you’re almost 30. Don’t you think it’s time to find your significant other?

230
00:18:56,840 --> 00:19:00,760
Fah, I have to go now. Got another call.

231
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:04,360
Hey! I’m not done talking yet.

232
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:17,720
What’s the matter, Din? Don’t tell me Dad also called you.

233
00:19:19,320 --> 00:19:22,360
Aren’t you going to consider dating anyone for a bit?

234
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,320
Seriously!

235
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,840
It’s such a burden.

236
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:31,160
I can’t imagine what that person would be like.

237
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:35,600
But I can’t wait to see the person who can make your heart waver.

238
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,320
You’d better pin that hope on Lom.

239
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:46,280
So, is there anything else? I need to wrap up some work after this.

240
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:50,960
Listen, what I’ll be saying might sound nonsense to you.

241
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:53,960
But life isn’t just about work, Nam.

242
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:59,800
Life is like a flower. A soil alone can’t make the flower bloom.

243
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:04,720
You also need fertilizer. Love is a good fertilizer for your life, Nam.

244
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,960
Hello? Din? Hello?

245
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:09,960
Can’t hear you. I’ll call you back.

246
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,160
[Rose]: 1 2 3!

247
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:15,240
[Moddang]: If you want to preserve it, just put a flower or two in a thick book and press them.

248
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:19,400
[Moddang]: Then leave it to dry. You can also frame it after that.

249
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:25,840
[Din]: Life is like a flower. A soil alone can’t make the flower bloom.

250
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:28,360
[Din]: You also need fertilizer.

251
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:38,200
Yes, I’m Chonlada Kunarnon. I called earlier for an appointment with Miss Apo.

252
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:46,080
Oh, I’m really sorry, Miss. Our boss has gone abroad. She won’t be back until the next two weeks.

253
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:48,760
Two weeks?

254
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,680
Yes, Miss.

255
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:53,040
Wow…

256
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:04,800
Nade, let’s check out what we can do here.

257
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,840
To kill our time for two weeks.

258
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:10,600
Hey! What now?

259
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,480
Just because you’re waiting to see her doesn’t mean she’d let you when she’s back.

260
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:18,040
You’re the guest but she’s the CEO.

261
00:22:18,040 --> 00:22:20,360
It’s not her job to take care of you.

262
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:28,440
You’re right. It’s useless to keep waiting like this.

263
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,320
You’re not up to something again, are you?

264
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:36,880
What? Of course not.

265
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:40,360
You told me to go home. I’m doing it.

266
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,760
Or do you want me to stay?

267
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:46,560
No! Let’s go back. Get in the car.

268
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,800
I heard you.

269
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:48,880
Quick!

270
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:56,840
Hey, get in the car.

271
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:58,080
Aha.

272
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,360
Let’s go.

273
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:33,400
Hello, Boss. Why are you back so early?

274
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:37,320
The other party couldn’t come to the meeting so I postponed it.

275
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:39,600
Why? What’s the problem?

276
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:44,280
There’s a guest who wishes to see you but she just checked out a minute ago.

277
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,280
A guest wants to see me?

278
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:51,320
She said it’s about her phone getting broken because of you.

279
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:55,800
Probably that lady who dropped her phone because you accidentally walked into her.

280
00:23:57,120 --> 00:24:00,760
I remember that. But I can’t remember her face.

281
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,520
She looks…

282
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:03,720
Never mind.

283
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:07,920
Please take care of it for me. If it’s not work, I’d rather not waste my time on it.

284
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:22,280
What happened? What’s wrong, Lada?

285
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:26,960
I got a job, Mum!

286
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:29,320
You got a job? What job, dear?

287
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:34,360
Please don’t worry, Aunt Mon.

288
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,800
I won’t tell Dad that she’s working at my hotel.

289
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:39,480
Not until she can stand on her own legs.

290
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:41,920
So that she can prove to him that she’s better than he thought.

291
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,400
Please don’t tell Dad too.

292
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:44,960
Okay.

293
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:55,680
While I’m away, you have to take good care of yourself.

294
00:24:56,720 --> 00:25:00,880
Don’t worry about me, dear. You might be away but I still have Nade.

295
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,880
Nade probably won’t come here for a while, Mum.

296
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:07,920
Huh, why not?

297
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,960
We’re having a row.

298
00:25:13,560 --> 00:25:14,480
Again?

299
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,840
We’ll make up soon.

300
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:38,760
Good, don’t you ever text me anything.

301
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:42,320
Because even if you did, I would never read it!

302
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,120
[Incoming message notification]

303
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:59,160
[Lada: On my way to Prachuap. Thanks a lot for the idea.]

304
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:04,640
What the? What is she talking about?!

305
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:12,560
Is it okay there?

306
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:16,120
I’m sorry but I really can’t let you stay at our hotel.

307
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:17,440
People might find it suspicious.

308
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:22,680
Don’t worry. I’m good here. This place is close to her hotel too.

309
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:27,280
I’ll try to get close to her the soonest I can. Definitely before the next land bidding.

310
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:31,760
This time, you’ll surely beat the Watin Group.

311
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:36,160
Thanks a lot, Lada.

312
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:38,760
[Lada]: No problem. Talk to you later.

313
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:50,800
Miss Chonlada. Miss Maythavee.

314
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:54,760
I hope both of you will follow all the rules and regulations as informed earlier.

315
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:59,960
And dedicate yourself to work for the Watin Group to prove that we have not made the wrong decision.

316
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:03,080
Yes, Miss Wadee.

317
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:06,600
Off you go to get on with your duty.

318
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:09,600
Each of you will have a mentor to help give you advice.

319
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:13,000
Wait, Miss Wadee.

320
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:17,240
Don’t you recognise me?

321
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,920
Oh! It’s you!

322
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,600
Well, you told me that Miss Apo went…

323
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:30,280
No! It’s ‘Boss’ for her.

324
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:34,240
Everyone here calls her ‘Boss’.

325
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:35,360
Not by her name.

326
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:40,440
I see. That day, you said Boss went abroad.

327
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,720
I’d like to know if she’s back now?

328
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,800
Don’t be so obvious.

329
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,640
Obvious about what?

330
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:58,280
It’s your first day at work and you’re already asking for the hotel owner.

331
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,720
What do you want me to think?

332
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,840
Where are you going? / - Are you two Lada and Vee?

333
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:17,640
Hello, I’m Maythavee.

334
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:19,800
Miss…

335
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:23,800
Nussara.

336
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,200
You can call me Nuch.

337
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:27,320
Miss Wadee has asked me to mentor you.

338
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:35,560
So, Vee…Wow, you used to be an intern at a hotel abroad for 3 years.

339
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:38,360
You can even speak 5 languages!

340
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:41,440
Oh dear, will I lose my job then?

341
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:46,800
I believe that knowing many languages is an advantage for working in this field.

342
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,760
It allows us to communicate with guests from all over the world.

343
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:57,440
That’s great. And Lada…You just graduated?

344
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:03,040
Yes. Is there any problem with that?

345
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:08,080
I’m just amazed. We’ve never hired a new-grad before.

346
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,960
Usually, they must have at least one year of experience.

347
00:29:10,960 --> 00:29:13,760
Vee did her internship after she graduated.

348
00:29:13,760 --> 00:29:16,760
But you got to be an intern while you were still studying abroad.

349
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:19,760
And you can even speak 8 languages!

350
00:29:20,080 --> 00:29:21,400
Amazing indeed.

351
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:30,120
But studying is completely different from working in real life.

352
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:33,240
I’d really appreciate your advice while working here.

353
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:36,720
Of course. Shall we start then?

354
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:40,040
Well, may I…use the toilet first?

355
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:43,120
Sure. But please make it quick.

356
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:45,800
Yes.

357
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:50,280
Let’s go, Vee.

358
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:08,560
You should be more careful. What if you walk into the guest?

359
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:11,240
We finally met.

360
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:17,400
Don’t tell me you can’t remember me.

361
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:25,360
Here…Do you remember now, Miss Apo?

362
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,800
Why are you wearing my hotel uniform?

363
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:37,600
Well, that’s because I’m employed here.

364
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:41,400
So, you remember me now, don’t you?

365
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:46,120
About your phone, I already told my secretary to take care of it.

366
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:52,800
As an executive of a big hotel, shouldn’t you be more responsible for this?

367
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,720
Besides, you should…

368
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:56,400
[Phone ringing]

369
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:01,840
Okay, I’ll be right there.

370
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:05,720
I’ll send you a new phone.

371
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:10,240
Hope that’ll make you satisfied. Now, you’d better spend more time focusing on work.

372
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,200
What do you want?

373
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:17,840
I don’t want a new phone.

374
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:20,680
I want you to treat me to a meal.

375
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:26,040
You can go eat whatever you want, and put the bill on my tab.

376
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:35,240
What?

377
00:31:37,480 --> 00:31:38,560
Don’t you feel it?

378
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:40,160
Feel what?

379
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:44,320
When our hands touched earlier, I could feel an electric shock.

380
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,240
Or is there a leakage around here?

381
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,840
I want to have a meal with you.

382
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,640
Hey, are you even listening?

383
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:07,200
I’m sorry but I don’t usually eat with strangers.

384
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:12,080
Not to mention you’re also an employee here. I don’t see why we should get acquainted.

385
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,800
Geez…

386
00:32:21,240 --> 00:32:24,760
I’ll make you see why, Miss Apo.

387
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:31,920
That’s right. Then greet the guests and ask for their ID cards.

388
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:36,640
Once done, fill in all the information and scan your ID.

389
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:42,800
Then inform the guests about our facilities, breakfast time, and so on.

390
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:48,680
What’s wrong, Lada?

391
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:51,320
Why are you looking so grumpy?

392
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:55,800
As a receptionist, it’s crucial to have control over your emotions.

393
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:59,240
Our lady boss might appear out of nowhere and evaluate us anytime.

394
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:02,880
That’s why we must always be prepared.

395
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:08,800
Nuch, can I ask you something?

396
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:13,760
Our boss, what kind of person is she like?

397
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:17,840
It’s just…I don’t want to get fired on my first day at work.

398
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:22,000
She doesn’t like mistakes, or rule breakers.

399
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:27,120
Exactly. You surely came well prepared.

400
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:30,240
Is she that strict?

401
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:34,960
Usually, she would give people who make their first mistake a second chance.

402
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:41,400
But if there’s a second time, you’d better start looking for a new job. You’ll surely get sacked.

403
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:44,400
Make sure you always follow the rules, Miss Lada.

404
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:52,960
Oh, good morning, sir. Welcome to Monarch International hotel.

405
00:34:04,640 --> 00:34:06,360
[Nuch]: Please wait a moment for the receipt.

406
00:34:08,159 --> 00:34:09,880
Lada!

407
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,280
Please go change right now! Hurry up!

408
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:22,719
Why, Nuch? I’m wearing the hotel uniform, aren’t I?

409
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:26,280
What? But what you’re doing is against the rules.

410
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:30,000
Every hotel staff must wear their hair up whether it’s short or long.

411
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:34,239
Why are you letting your hair down like this? Oh dear, I’m going to faint.

412
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:36,840
Why? I think it looks nice.

413
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:37,600
Oh dear.

414
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:40,560
You can’t do that. The rules say it must be all black.

415
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:44,800
But your heels are bright red, just like your lips colour.

416
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:51,320
Red lips and red shoes, don’t you think they go well together? It kind of makes me look fierce.

417
00:34:52,639 --> 00:34:58,600
My goodness. If you still want to pass the probation, you’d better hurry and get changed. Quick! Go now!

418
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,400
Why should I?

419
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:04,760
Please go ahead.

420
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:11,520
[Nussara]: This is bad. / - [Wadee]: Yeah.

421
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:17,160
Thank you. Please don’t forget to hashtag our hotel’s name.

422
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:18,240
[Guest]: Sure.

423
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:19,880
Thank you.

424
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:22,480
See? Our guests seem to like it.

425
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:26,280
You still can’t. The guests might like it but our boss doesn’t!

426
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:27,840
That employee over there.

427
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:55,360
Those who are not involved, get back to your work.

428
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:56,400
[Wadee/Nussara]: Yes, Boss!

429
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,720
As for you…

430
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:25,760
Why would you want to talk to me, Boss? Have I done anything wrong?

431
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:40,160
Tell me, from your head to toe,

432
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,760
is there anywhere that complies with the rules?

433
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:47,440
Well, there’s nothing wrong though.

434
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:50,560
Beauty is also important, Boss.

435
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:55,080
I believe having confidence in what you’re wearing at work could help give a better performance.

436
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:58,240
But we don’t welcome pretty faces with no brains here.

437
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:10,240
I have brains too, not just beauty.

438
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:19,680
And as the rules say that we should pay attention to cleanliness and hygiene…

439
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:22,200
Do I not look clean enough?

440
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:26,720
Or maybe…do you want to have a closer look and check…

441
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:33,120
whether I smell good or not?

442
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:51,160
I have something to show you.

443
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:58,800
Look, our guest posted it. But it might be a bit blurry.

444
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:02,520
Because someone dropped my phone and refused to take responsibility.

445
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:03,720
I took responsibility.

446
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:11,640
Our guest posted this picture with a hashtag on our hotel’s name. Many people seem to like it.

447
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:16,400
Will you still say…that I’m pretty but brainless?

448
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:23,280
Dressing up prettily to create content and get more exposure for our hotel, isn’t that a good thing?

449
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,760
Don’t you agree?

450
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:35,680
Miss Preem.

451
00:38:36,840 --> 00:38:37,480
Miss Preem!

452
00:38:37,480 --> 00:38:38,600
Yes, Boss?

453
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:49,640
From tomorrow on, don’t ever let me see this employee in my hotel again!

454
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:02,480
Hey! Stop right there! Hey!

455
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:04,080
Stop! Stop right there!

456
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:06,400
I said stop! Stop, stop, stop!

457
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:08,280
Stop right now!

458
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:10,000
I’m not quitting!

459
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:12,160
[Preem]: Please stop! / - [Lada]: No, I won’t!

460
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:16,480
Boss, please get on with your work. Let me handle this.

461
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:23,360
Is this the lady boss that people claim to be so talented?

462
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:24,400
It seems to me…

463
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,360
that you’re just a loser! / - Hey!

464
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:32,520
Leave it to me.

465
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,200
But you have an appointment, Boss.

466
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:41,280
Hand me the personnel document.

467
00:39:50,680 --> 00:39:54,960
Miss Chonlada Kunarnon. Have you read your employment contract?

468
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:57,280
Have you read every line written in there?

469
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:03,800
Yes, I have. But I don’t see any clause saying I couldn’t wear my makeup like this.

470
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:16,360
This line here stated that…if you ever break the rules…

471
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:19,720
or violate the Watin Group’s regulations,

472
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:21,960
your employment will be terminated immediately.

473
00:40:22,680 --> 00:40:27,320
Even though it’s not written here directly that you can’t wear makeup like this,

474
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:30,960
if you still insist that you have some brains.

475
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:35,800
you’d see that what you’re doing is wrong. Don’t try to dodge it.

476
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:39,080
But I didn’t see this line when I signed the contract.

477
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:42,680
Wait! Did you two play dirty and add it after I signed?

478
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:46,920
Really? Did you even read it at all?

479
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:53,720
What kind of a pretty face couldn’t even read more than 8 lines?

480
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:55,080
Boss!

481
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:57,840
I have two options for you.

482
00:40:57,840 --> 00:41:03,320
Submit your resignation, or I’ll announce that your employment is terminated.

483
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:07,400
Pick your choice, and let me know.

484
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:11,960
You!

485
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:16,440
What? What are you looking at?

486
00:41:26,080 --> 00:41:29,080
Hey, wait! Stop!

487
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:38,160
[Preem]: Hey! Stop it!

488
00:41:38,160 --> 00:41:41,160
Miss Preem! / - No! Don’t come in.

489
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:44,160
Don’t come in. Stay right there.

490
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,360
Boss!

491
00:41:58,280 --> 00:41:59,720
What are you doing?

492
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:11,080
Since we’re humans, we all make mistakes, right?

493
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:15,840
Don’t you think firing me would be a wrong decision?

494
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,200
All my life, I’ve never made a wrong decision.

495
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:21,880
This is my first time making a mistake though.

496
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:27,280
I heard you always give those who make their first mistake a second chance. Isn’t that right?

497
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:31,240
Well, yes. But not with you.

498
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:35,800
Wait, listen…

499
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:42,040
Boss. Please give me a chance to prove to you that I’m also capable at work.

500
00:42:42,520 --> 00:42:46,360
I don’t want you to think that I’m pretty but brainless.

501
00:42:46,720 --> 00:42:52,520
I promise that if I ever break one more rule again, I’ll quit this job right away.

502
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:55,200
I said no! Don’t you get it?

503
00:42:55,520 --> 00:42:57,600
Then I’ll sit here until the lift door opens.

504
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:59,760
Let everyone see us like this.

505
00:43:00,360 --> 00:43:03,640
This time, it’s you whose reputation would be ruined.

506
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:05,080
You!

507
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:09,280
Shit!

508
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:16,200
You can try all you want, but they will see us anyway.

509
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:17,680
There.

510
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,280
And there.

511
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:23,760
Now, only those in the control room can see us.

512
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:26,440
I can still fix this rumour for you.

513
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:29,440
But once the door opens at the lobby,

514
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:34,880
I can’t imagine how I could stop the rumour to save your and your hotel’s reputations.

515
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:41,200
Okay, fine!

516
00:43:41,200 --> 00:43:43,880
I’ll give you a chance. Can you get up now?

517
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:47,560
Hang on. Please wait.

518
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:51,440
What did you just say, Boss? Hang on.

519
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:56,000
Can you say it again? Please look at the camera too.

520
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:57,000
Why?

521
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:01,840
So that I’ll have proof…that I’m not a pretty face with no brains.

522
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:06,760
So…what now?

523
00:44:07,560 --> 00:44:09,600
I’ll give you a chance!

524
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:11,840
Hmm, I can’t hear it.

525
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:14,400
Chonlada.

526
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:19,400
Make it loud and clear, Boss.

527
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:22,800
I’ll give you a chance, Chonlada! Satisfied now?

528
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:25,280
That’s it.

529
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:30,240
I promise that I will not disappoint you, Boss.

530
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:37,280
From tomorrow on, I’ll have someone to keep an eye on you.

531
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:41,080
If you mess up again, you’re out!

532
00:44:54,560 --> 00:44:55,960
Thank you.

533
00:44:55,960 --> 00:44:58,760
[Guest]: Girl, can you tell me where the toilet is?

534
00:44:58,760 --> 00:45:00,040
[Chonlada]: A toilet?

535
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:01,440
[Guest]: We need to go to the loo.

536
00:45:01,440 --> 00:45:04,320
[Guest]: Excuse me, can you take a picture for me?

537
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:09,160
[Guest]: - Which restaurant is the best around here? / - Please tell us where the toilet is. / - Can you take a picture for us?

538
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:12,160
[Guest]: I can’t hold it in anymore!

539
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:13,720
[Guest]: We need to go to the loo.

540
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:20,760
Everyone! Please listen!

541
00:45:20,760 --> 00:45:22,760
Listen, everyone. You need a toilet, right?

542
00:45:22,760 --> 00:45:23,200
[Guest]: Yes.

543
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:25,200
Please go straight that way and turn right.

544
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:27,600
[Guest]: Okay, thanks a lot! / - My pleasure.

545
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:28,840
Just a moment please.

546
00:45:29,160 --> 00:45:30,560
The restaurant, right? / - Yes!

547
00:45:30,560 --> 00:45:33,160
Please try this one out. It’s a five-star guarantee.

548
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:34,360
Thank you.

549
00:45:34,360 --> 00:45:35,400
Can you take a picture for me? / - All of you together?

550
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:37,480
[Guest]: Yes, thank you. / - Okay.

551
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:43,280
1 2 3…Cheese!

552
00:45:43,280 --> 00:45:46,280
There you go. Thank you.

553
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:06,600
[Wadee/Nussara]: Well done!

554
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:27,280
[Guest]: Hey, I haven’t done talking yet!

555
00:46:27,280 --> 00:46:31,920
[Wadee]: Sir, I’m so sorry but I’m not interested in you. Could you please let me go?

556
00:46:31,920 --> 00:46:32,840
[Guest]: No, no, let’s…/ - [Wadee]: Sir!

557
00:46:32,840 --> 00:46:34,800
[Wadee]: You have to let me go. / - [Lada]: Stop!

558
00:46:35,320 --> 00:46:38,600
[Guest]: What? How dare you do this to your guest?

559
00:46:38,600 --> 00:46:42,840
I’ll complain to your manager. Call your manager!

560
00:46:42,840 --> 00:46:44,920
You have no right to do this to us staff,

561
00:46:45,520 --> 00:46:49,360
especially with girls. Learn to have some respect, please.

562
00:46:50,160 --> 00:46:54,160
[Guest]: What? What's happening? What's wrong?

563
00:46:55,040 --> 00:47:00,000
[The guest’s wife]: I’m so sorry about this. Sorry. I heard my husband is making a scene here. I’m sorry.

564
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:04,240
[The guest’s wife]: Jeremy, for God’s sake, sweetie.

565
00:47:04,240 --> 00:47:07,280
If you don’t stop this right now, they’re gonna call the cops.

566
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:12,800
[The guest’s wife]: I’m sorry. I’m so sorry. Thanks for understanding.

567
00:47:19,880 --> 00:47:22,240
Miss Wadee, are you all right?

568
00:47:22,960 --> 00:47:28,280
I’m all right, thank you. Did you tell that man’s wife to come and save me?

569
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:32,080
Yes.

570
00:47:33,120 --> 00:47:35,280
Thank you so much.

571
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:38,280
If it weren’t for you, I’d have been in so much trouble.

572
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:42,000
That’s all right.

573
00:48:44,480 --> 00:48:46,320
[Guest]: Have you found it?

574
00:48:46,320 --> 00:48:48,200
[Chonlada]: No, Miss.

575
00:48:48,920 --> 00:48:53,320
[Guest]: Please help me find it. Make sure you search every nook and cranny.

576
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:54,960
Yes, Miss.

577
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:59,040
[Guest B]: Please calm down.  They’ll definitely find it.

578
00:48:59,080 --> 00:49:00,360
[Guest A]: Okay.

579
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:03,840
[Guest A]: It’s really important to me.

580
00:49:03,840 --> 00:49:05,960
[Guest B]: Don’t worry. They’ll find it.

581
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:08,960
[Guest A]: My kids saved up and bought it for me.

582
00:49:09,280 --> 00:49:11,280
[Wadee]: We understand, Miss.

583
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:19,760
[Guest B]: Have you found it?

584
00:49:31,160 --> 00:49:32,760
Lada!

585
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:34,640
Did she just jump in?

586
00:49:38,440 --> 00:49:39,960
[Guest A]: Have you found it?

587
00:49:40,560 --> 00:49:43,080
[Guest A]: Is it in there? Is it?

588
00:49:43,600 --> 00:49:45,280
No, Miss.

589
00:49:45,360 --> 00:49:47,120
[Guest B]: It’s all right. We’ll find it soon.

590
00:49:54,760 --> 00:49:56,960
[Guest A/B]: Did you get it?

591
00:49:59,160 --> 00:50:00,640
[Guest A]: You didn’t find it, did you?

592
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:02,520
[Nussara]: Don’t give up, Lada!

593
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:04,840
[Nussara]: You can do it!

594
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,280
[Wadee]: Will she find it?

595
00:50:12,320 --> 00:50:13,840
[Nussara]: We believe in you!

596
00:50:16,600 --> 00:50:18,680
[Guest A]: Any sign of it?

597
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:28,040
[Guest A]: Yes! That’s the one!

598
00:50:28,040 --> 00:50:30,360
[Guest A]: Thank you so much! That’s mine!

599
00:50:31,000 --> 00:50:32,800
[Nussara]: Way to go!

600
00:50:34,720 --> 00:50:35,680
[Nussara]: You’re amazing!

601
00:50:35,680 --> 00:50:37,840
[Guest A]: Thank you so much!

602
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:43,720
[Apo]: If that’s all, please go ahead and wrap it up.

603
00:51:01,280 --> 00:51:02,760
[A plate clattering]

604
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:06,040
I’m sorry, Miss.

605
00:51:13,680 --> 00:51:16,360
You have another meeting at 2pm, Boss.

606
00:51:17,640 --> 00:51:19,400
How’s Chonlada?

607
00:51:20,560 --> 00:51:22,320
How’s who, Boss?

608
00:51:23,200 --> 00:51:25,560
That employee whose phone is broken because of me.

609
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:33,320
That’s the first employee you can remember her name.

610
00:51:36,640 --> 00:51:38,880
Has Miss Wadee submitted her evaluation?

611
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:41,720
She submitted it this morning, Boss.

612
00:51:43,920 --> 00:51:46,520
Miss Wadee has never let Miss Chonlada out of her sight.

613
00:51:46,520 --> 00:51:48,640
It seems she hasn’t made any mistakes so far.

614
00:51:56,760 --> 00:51:59,160
But if you want me to find an excuse to fire her…

615
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:04,840
No need. Keep reporting me as it is. Don’t be biased.

616
00:52:07,520 --> 00:52:09,080
Yes, Boss.

617
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:31,000
[Pheempat]: So, Apo decided not to fire you, right?

618
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:39,360
I don’t know. But I won’t let her fire me so easily. Not until I can get more information for you.

619
00:52:40,840 --> 00:52:43,440
That’s why I’m here.

620
00:52:43,440 --> 00:52:45,960
In a few months, we’ll enter the low season.

621
00:52:45,960 --> 00:52:49,400
I want to find out how Apo is planning to attract more guests.

622
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:52,120
A plan to attract more guests?

623
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:53,640
Yes.

624
00:52:54,440 --> 00:52:57,880
All these years, we’ve always been one step behind the Watin Group.

625
00:52:57,880 --> 00:52:59,600
They always get the biggest chunk of meat.

626
00:52:59,600 --> 00:53:02,280
I want our attraction plan to be different from theirs.

627
00:53:03,120 --> 00:53:06,720
So that we can earn more trust from Dad while waiting for the land bidding.

628
00:53:07,440 --> 00:53:09,440
Is there any way I can help?

629
00:53:20,800 --> 00:53:22,280
Lada.

630
00:53:22,920 --> 00:53:26,880
I’m thinking I’ll switch to a night shift next month.

631
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:29,440
Huh? Why?

632
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:32,680
Don’t you enjoy working the day shift?

633
00:53:32,760 --> 00:53:38,160
Well, lately our boss often appears out of nowhere to evaluate us. It makes me anxious.

634
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:42,840
Especially on days that I have to work with you, she’ll always show up.

635
00:53:44,480 --> 00:53:47,000
Probably to check if I’m messing up.

636
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:50,800
Because if I ever did, she’ll definitely kick me out.

637
00:53:52,440 --> 00:53:57,440
But I don’t think so. Otherwise, you wouldn’t have made it this far after many weeks.

638
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:04,520
You’re more talented than I thought. And I’m sure Boss also thinks the same.

639
00:54:06,560 --> 00:54:09,560
Is there any position that allows me to get close to Boss?

640
00:54:10,240 --> 00:54:11,520
What was that again?

641
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:13,720
Nothing. Just forget it.

642
00:54:13,800 --> 00:54:17,280
I asked because I’ll try to avoid taking that position.

643
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:20,800
Shall we get back to work then?

644
00:54:21,080 --> 00:54:22,880
Sure, let’s go.

645
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:31,440
Isn’t that Miss Wayo?

646
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:01,040
Oh, Lom?

647
00:55:01,040 --> 00:55:02,520
Miss you!

648
00:55:02,520 --> 00:55:04,720
Geez, Lom!

649
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:09,000
My suit will get wrinkled. Behave yourself.

650
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:10,360
How did you get here?

651
00:55:10,360 --> 00:55:12,160
The thought of you brought me here.

652
00:55:12,560 --> 00:55:13,760
Be serious.

653
00:55:14,160 --> 00:55:16,240
I really miss you.

654
00:55:17,640 --> 00:55:19,160
Don’t you have work to do?

655
00:55:19,640 --> 00:55:25,560
I do. But I’m a happyholic, not a workaholic like you.

656
00:55:26,160 --> 00:55:28,760
It’s a holiday. Let me take a break somehow.

657
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:35,800
Do cops also have holidays?

658
00:55:36,560 --> 00:55:39,360
Of course, every job has holidays.

659
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:44,160
It’s up to us whether we’ll use them or not. Wanna go out?

660
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:50,280
I have a meeting. If you’re free, just go see Din then. Let her take you around.

661
00:55:50,280 --> 00:55:54,560
Have you got a room? I’ll tell Miss Preem to take care of it.

662
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:57,160
I gotta go.

663
00:55:57,160 --> 00:55:58,960
Geez, wait!

664
00:55:58,960 --> 00:56:00,240
What?

665
00:56:00,840 --> 00:56:04,960
You’re an executive. Can’t you just give orders and let others do the work?

666
00:56:06,800 --> 00:56:11,440
And give my employees a reason to talk behind my back that I’m irresponsible? No!

667
00:56:11,440 --> 00:56:16,160
Hold on! How about this? If you don’t want to go out, let’s have a meal together.

668
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:21,080
Pleaseeee. I’ve driven all the way here.

669
00:56:24,440 --> 00:56:25,680
Give me half an hour.

670
00:56:25,680 --> 00:56:27,080
20 minutes then.

671
00:56:27,720 --> 00:56:29,600
No arguing. Come, it’s a deal.

672
00:56:29,600 --> 00:56:31,800
I’ll hang around downstairs while waiting for you.

673
00:56:31,800 --> 00:56:33,680
After you, Boss.

674
00:56:35,360 --> 00:56:37,120
Let’s get you to work.

675
00:56:40,880 --> 00:56:43,880
[Chonlada]: What is Miss Wayo doing here?

676
00:56:44,280 --> 00:56:48,240
[Nussara]: She’s probably on her day off. It’s her family’s hotel anyway.

677
00:56:48,640 --> 00:56:51,840
I think she’ll probably be staying at our hotel.

678
00:56:51,840 --> 00:56:54,840
Those staff on the night shift will definitely get to see her.

679
00:56:55,360 --> 00:56:56,280
I see.

680
00:56:56,800 --> 00:57:01,840
Nuch, what if I want to try working a night shift, is that possible?

681
00:57:02,440 --> 00:57:06,720
I just want to know what it’d be like.

682
00:57:07,400 --> 00:57:09,680
Can you possibly squeeze me in?

683
00:57:09,880 --> 00:57:12,880
Don’t tell me you’ve fallen for Miss Wayo’s charm too.

684
00:57:13,960 --> 00:57:16,960
Our boss’s sister is very charming indeed.

685
00:57:19,720 --> 00:57:25,720
Are you a newbie? I’ve never seen you here before.

686
00:57:33,720 --> 00:57:37,920
You mightn’t recognise me. But I have seen you before.

687
00:57:38,760 --> 00:57:40,320
From where?

688
00:57:45,680 --> 00:57:48,200
[Chonlada]: Okay, bye!

689
00:57:54,600 --> 00:57:56,720
[Pui]: Thank you.

690
00:57:57,920 --> 00:57:59,720
[Wayo]: Please close your eyes.

691
00:58:02,640 --> 00:58:04,320
Now, open them.

692
00:58:04,800 --> 00:58:06,800
[Pui]: Aww, so cute!

693
00:58:06,800 --> 00:58:08,840
Do you like it? / Yes.

694
00:58:11,320 --> 00:58:12,520
Thank you.

695
00:58:14,440 --> 00:58:17,440
Well, you just walked past by earlier, Miss Wayo.

696
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:21,280
You know my name?

697
00:58:22,240 --> 00:58:25,240
Who wouldn’t know the name of Boss’s younger sister?

698
00:58:26,520 --> 00:58:29,520
Anyway, is there anything I can help?

699
00:58:31,160 --> 00:58:34,160
Well, my room is all taken care of.

700
00:58:35,200 --> 00:58:42,920
But for other things, I’m not sure if you’d be able to help, Miss Chonlada.

701
00:58:44,480 --> 00:58:47,240
You can call me Lada.

702
00:58:48,040 --> 00:58:50,000
I don’t have any friends here.

703
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:53,840
Can you be my friend, Lada?

704
00:59:03,760 --> 00:59:05,720
Just a friend?

705
00:59:09,720 --> 00:59:11,320
Lom!

706
00:59:13,520 --> 00:59:14,720
Huh?

707
00:59:15,680 --> 00:59:18,920
I thought you said 20 minutes. It’s been only 10 minutes.

708
00:59:21,280 --> 00:59:23,000
What are you doing?

709
00:59:23,000 --> 00:59:27,240
I just…asked Lada to help me find the room. I want the key card.

710
00:59:32,760 --> 00:59:37,600
Tell Miss Wadee to take care of her room. And leave the key card with Miss Preem.

711
00:59:37,600 --> 00:59:39,280
Yes, Boss.

712
00:59:57,280 --> 00:59:58,480
Sis…

713
00:59:58,800 --> 01:00:00,760
How long has Lada been working here?

714
01:00:00,760 --> 01:00:03,880
I came here so many times but I’ve never seen her before.

715
01:00:03,880 --> 01:00:05,280
Not long.

716
01:00:06,200 --> 01:00:09,920
How long were you talking to Chonlada? How did you know her nickname?

717
01:00:10,280 --> 01:00:13,440
Hang on. You remember her name?

718
01:00:14,600 --> 01:00:16,680
You usually can’t remember your employee’s name.

719
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:20,320
Even for Miss Preem, it took you months to remember her name.

720
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:23,600
We had a bit of an issue.

721
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:24,680
What is it?

722
01:00:26,600 --> 01:00:27,720
Why would you want to know?

723
01:00:27,720 --> 01:00:31,360
Well, if it’s about her, I want to know.

724
01:00:32,000 --> 01:00:33,960
Why would you want to know about her?

725
01:00:36,800 --> 01:00:38,760
I want to ask her out.

726
01:00:39,960 --> 01:00:41,240
You can’t!

727
01:00:43,120 --> 01:00:44,800
I must have misheard it.

728
01:00:44,800 --> 01:00:46,480
Did you just stop me?

729
01:00:48,840 --> 01:00:53,160
She’s my employee. You can’t do that.

730
01:00:54,400 --> 01:00:56,720
You’ve never said that before.

731
01:00:56,720 --> 01:01:01,320
